President Donald Trump on Tuesday vetoed a resolution to end U.S. support of Saudi Arabia’s military campaign in Yemen, which has been blamed for tens of thousands of deaths in the region.
The Senate passed the resolution by a slim majority in March, and the House did the same earlier this month.
The war in Yemen has caused the worst humanitarian crisis in the world.
“We remain keenly aware that a sustainable peace ... would be the most effective remedy for the humanitarian crisis in Yemen,” Mark Lowcock, the U.N. humanitarian chief, said this week.
Barring changes, the end is nigh.”This article has been updated with responses from House Speaker Nancy Pelosi and Sen. Chris Murphy.